      • getId

        public java.lang.String getId()
        Description copied from interface: TestEngine
        Get the ID that uniquely identifies this test engine.

        Each test engine must provide a unique ID. JUnit 4 and 5 use "junit4" and "junit5", respectively. When in doubt, you may use the fully qualified name of your custom TestEngine implementation class.

      • discover

        public TestDescriptor discover(EngineDiscoveryRequest discoveryRequest,
                               UniqueId uniqueId)
        Description copied from interface: TestEngine
        Discover tests according to an EngineDiscoveryRequest.

        The supplied uniqueId must be used for the returned TestDescriptor. In addition, it is used to create unique IDs for its children by calling UniqueId.append(java.lang.String, java.lang.String).

        Parameters:
        discoveryRequest - the request to discover tests from
        uniqueId - the unique ID to be used for this test engine's TestDescriptor
        Returns:
        the root TestDescriptor of this engine
